{
  "stem": "19211.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I'm just telling you from experience, we have no other choice.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Jewish people, they only want their own land.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's the only way that we can survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Otherwise it's-- it's-- it's problems.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's a possibility.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Look what happened.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Germany was excellent, was wonderful to the Jewish people, excellent.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And look what happened, in 19-- when Hitler came to power.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He poisoned most of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's what happened, the worst country in the whole world, for the Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was the-- one of the best, best democracies.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Funny thing happens now.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because I go to shul.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In Germany, they used to have the prayer for our country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Jews, when you live in the country, become a citizen of the country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you're part of it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was a prayer for our country.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, when I say that prayer for our country, even now I think about all the non-Jews that are again-- I'm sorry I'm telling you my inner feelings now.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Is it worth saying that for our-- is it our country?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know anymore.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm getting senile.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't trust people as much as I used to.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, it's-- it's difficult.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When you go to a lot like that, there are a very few people that I would trust that are non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of them was Garafalo.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was just a wonderful father, some wonderful people here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But you don't know who to trust anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When you saw Germans turns over-- turn over in the night, they were your friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I forgot to tell you that, one other story.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in-- when we lived in Brody, when the Germans took over, we-- my-- we lived like, in a duplex, or a triplex even, there was another family.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
